<div type="definition">
<p>SPEAK:say that something that has been SAID is UNTRUE.</p>
    <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2023-09-13T01:28:13.214+09:00">
            <p>SPEAK:say that SOMETHING is NOT TRUE.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There are no common words for denial in pre-Buddhist Chinese. Fēi 非 has declarative transitive uses, I think, but I have not yet identified a clear relevant example.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>否定 is the current modern word for denial.</p>
<p>否決 is to make or pass a decision against something.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
